objects.definition: Use to indicate a relation to the work that the resource is citing/quoting.
objects.name: Cites

objects.definition: One to many relationship that denotes that the one source resource has been assembled from the target resources through a process of integration and harmonization (as opposed to simple aggregation).
objects.name: Compiles

objects.definition: Use to indicate the resource is a continuation of the work referenced by the related identifier.
objects.name: Continues

objects.definition: Use to indicate the relation to the work which is documentation.
objects.name: Documents

objects.definition: Use to indicate the resource is a container of another resource.
objects.name: Has part

objects.definition: Used to indicate that one entity is attached to another. For example this term can be used to express the fact that a piece of equipment is attached to a related piece of equipment.
objects.name: Is attached to

objects.definition: Used to indicate that one entity is an immediate child of another entity. For example, this term can be used to express the fact that an instrument deployment Action is the child of a site visit Action.
objects.name: Is child of

objects.definition: Used to indicate the relationship between a Citation and the entity for which it is the Citation.
objects.name: Is citation for

objects.definition: Use to indicate the relation to a work that cites/quotes this data.
objects.name: Is cited by

objects.definition: Use to indicate the resource or data is compiled/created by using another resource or dataset.
objects.name: Is compiled by

objects.definition: Use to indicate the resource is continued by the work referenced by the related identifier.
objects.name: Is continued by

objects.definition: Used to indicate the relation to the works from which the resource was derived.
objects.name: Is derived from
objects.note: Used for related Results and related Datasets.

objects.definition: Use to indicate the work is documentation about/explaining the resource referenced by the related identifier.
objects.name: Is documented by

objects.definition: Used to indicate the relation to a work that is identical to the resource.
objects.name: Is identical to

objects.definition: Use to indicate the resource is a new edition of an old resource, where the new edition has been modified or updated.
objects.name: Is new version of

objects.definition: Use to indicate the relation to the works which are variant or different forms of the resource.
objects.name: Is original form of

objects.definition: Use to indicate the resource is a portion of another resource.
objects.name: Is part of

objects.definition: Use to indicate the resource is a previous edition of a newer resource.
objects.name: Is previous version of

objects.definition: Use to indicate the resource is used as a source of information by another resource.
objects.name: Is referenced by

objects.definition: Used to indicate that one entity has a complex relationship with another entity that is not a simple, hierarchical parent-child relationship. For example, this term can be used to express the fact that an instrument cleaning Action is related to an instrument deployment action even though it may be performed as part of a separate site visit.
objects.name: Is related to

objects.definition: Use to indicate the action is a retrieval of a previous deployment.
objects.name: Is retrieval for
objects.note: This is necessary for proper implementation of deployments and retrievals in the ODM2 Equipment schema.

objects.definition: Used to indicate that the work is reviewed by another resource.
objects.name: Is reviewed by

objects.definition: Used to indicate the relation to the works that were the source of the resource.
objects.name: Is source of
objects.note: Used for related Results, related Datasets, and related Citations.

objects.definition: Use to indicate the relation to the work to which the resource is a supplement.
objects.name: Is supplement to

objects.definition: Use to indicate the relation to the work(s) which are supplements of the resource.
objects.name: Is supplemented by

objects.definition: Use to indicate the resource is a variant or different form of another resource, e.g. calculated or calibrated form or different packaging.
objects.name: Is variant form of

objects.definition: Use to indicate the relation to the work which is used as a source of information of the resource.
objects.name: References

objects.definition: Used to indicate that the work reviews another resource.
objects.name: Reviews

objects.definition: Used to indicate that one entity was collected at the location of another entity. For example, thirs term can be used to express the fact that a specimen SamplingFeature was collected at a site SamplingFeature.
objects.name: Was collected at
